  "tell us about one system/project you\u2019ve built that you\u2019re proud of.\n(focus on what you designed, what broke, and how you fixed it.)": "One project I\u2019m proud of is Jewel Track, a full-stack jewellery business management system I built using React, Node.js, Express, and MongoDB. I designed it to handle customer records, billing, and order tracking in a simple way for real daily use. One issue I faced was slow data retrieval and messy data flow as records increased. I fixed this by improving the database schema, optimizing queries, and restructuring APIs for better performance and consistency.\n\nI also built a Form Filling Agent using LangChain and LangGraph, where I designed a workflow to understand user input and automatically fill complex web forms. Initially, the responses were inconsistent due to unstructured prompts. I fixed this by improving prompt design, adding structured outputs, and controlling the flow using LangGraph, which made the system more reliable.\n\nThese projects helped me understand both system design and how to debug and improve real-world applications.",
  "suppose you have 8 gpus and multiple users submitting inference jobs with different latency requirements.\nhow would you think about scheduling and utilization?": "I would first separate jobs based on latency requirements into real-time and batch. I\u2019d reserve some GPUs for low-latency tasks and use the rest for batch jobs to maintain good utilization. I\u2019d use priority-based scheduling so urgent requests are handled first, and apply batching for similar jobs to improve GPU efficiency. If needed, I\u2019d allow preemption so high-priority jobs can use GPUs immediately. This way I can balance latency and utilization effectively.",
  "have you worked on anything related to performance optimization (latency, throughput, memory, etc.)? briefly explain.": "Yes. In my projects like Quick Serve and Jewel Track, I worked on performance optimization mainly around API response time and database efficiency. I optimized queries, improved data flow, and reduced unnecessary API calls from the frontend. I also structured components better in React to avoid unnecessary re-renders. These changes helped reduce latency and made the applications faster and more stable for real users.",
