  "share a project you've built (personal/hackathon/college). what was the hardest technical problem you faced and how did you solve it?": "One project I built is a Form Filling Agent using LangChain and LangGraph. The hardest problem I faced was around usability. Initially, users had to log in again whenever a new tab opened, and they also had to manually paste the form link, which made the experience slow and frustrating. To solve this, I built a browser extension that keeps the session active and directly works on the current form page.",
  "what's the most interesting technical thing you've learned or built in the last 3 months? why did it excite you?": "In the last 3 months, the most interesting thing I built is a Form Filling Agent using LLMs with LangChain and LangGraph. It can understand user input and automatically fill complex web forms. What made it exciting for me was seeing how AI can actually automate real tasks and improve user experience.",
  "github link": "https://github.com/Gaurav-meena95",
  "our dashboard is loading slowly when users filter through 50,000+ ads. walk through how you'd debug and optimize this.": "First, I would try to find where the issue is, whether it\u2019s frontend, backend, or database. On the backend, I would check the database queries. With 50,000+ ads, slow filtering can happen if queries are not optimised or indexes are missing. I would add proper indexes on filter fields and make sure we are not fetching unnecessary data. Then, I would use pagination instead of loading all data at once. This will reduce the load time a lot. I would also add caching for frequently used filters so we don\u2019t hit the database every time. On the frontend, I would make sure we are not rendering too many items together by using lazy loading or virtualisation.",
